The passionate post-war modern architecture, the clear shapes, the glass halls, the bold curves and the new building materials, typical of thinking about technical progress, for which, the Austrian pavilion by architect Karl Schwanzer for the 1958 Brussels Universal Exhibition is a fitting and well-known example.
