Its pavilion, designed as a temporary building for exhibitions was erected after the Universal Exhibition in the Schweizer Garten next to Vienna's South Station, was renovated in 1962 and inside a museum of the 20th century was opened, it was called the "house 20".
The building was adequate but lacked the space and technology for a museum; no walls to hang art, no good atmosphere.
Despite this it was used until contemporary art in Vienna had a new home.
The building has been empty since 2001 and is falling apart.
Currently, the pavilion has been renovated by architect Adolf Krischanitz, now calling it "house 21" and will be used in the future as a museum of contemporary art.
